      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the spirit within my breast. It is all for naught, isn't it? The betrayal, the silence of the manor, the hollow ache where my heart once beat for him... it's all become such a heavy, grey weight. I feel as though the very shadows of this room are calling to me, whispering that I needn't struggle against the tide any longer. There is a certain... peace, in the thought of simply ceasing to be. Just fading into the velvet dark, where no one can ever hurt me again.",
